<br>
ideas:<br>
<br>
-hidden crits ignore armor(partially, enough to be usefull vs light tanks or healers) Why factor armor I'm aiming for the opening. <br>
-they auto dual wield crits<br>
-auto get a crit on top of cs <br>
-they auto apply a double dot poison<br>
-stamina drain poisons that make it so a tank can still &quot;tank&quot; but can't turn around and do 2 anytime styles and drop you in 2 hits. Heck longer battles are more fun eh?<br>
-auto evade for 10 second, like a reverse beserker role(10 seconds of a skill similar to that shield block skill at the cost of no attacking and loss of stam, mostly a pve tweak)<br>
-meaningfull crit affects, real slow, stuns, aggro reductions<br>
-there are so many minor effects that could be added to crit lines to be usefull. As it is now is a combat skill of which require 2 of, and it does less than any style in the game except the ultimate perf style. I've tested I replace most every crit style with my thrust styles except the hidden ones. Give the in between styles some cool group uses.<br>
<br>
<br>
I can't think of anymore right now, I don't pretend these are all good ideas or we need them all, but maybe some skills to make us better for more than killing the same things as archers.<br>
<br>
Just saying maybe our problem is falling into the caster and grey/green killing role when we should look for something else. Like I said I'd trade MUCH more damage for losing our ignore bladeturn. As it is we are stuck in the role of being more usefull than an archer. How about instead of competing with an archer we come up with some nice skills that'll let us change our roles. Heck maybe its impossible to do this, this could me a useless rant, I'm just tired of looking at what archers can do, and honestlly realizing they do it mostly better than I do.<br>
